OL,3,CLoose Women launch domestic abuse
OL,4,Cawareness campaign in Belfast
OL,6,FLoose Women panelist Nadia Sawalha
OL,7,Ftold UTV: "This is an ongoing
OL,8,Fcampaign. It's backed by Parliament.
OL,9,FIt's really important because we want
OL,10,Fto keep getting that message out that
OL,11,Fyou're not alone.
OL,13,F"If every 16 minutes there's a phone
OL,14,Fcall about domestic abuse... what
OL,15,Fabout all the people that didn't call?
OL,17,F"Many women suffer in silence. And
OL,18,Fsome of them don't even know they are
OL,19,Fvictims of violence.
